## Stack

React 18, Vite 5, TypeScript, TanStack Query v5, React Router 6, Tailwind. Quality: `npm run ci`.

## Entry points

- `src/main.tsx`, `src/app/App.tsx`, `src/app/routes/appRoutes.tsx`
- Feature registry: `src/app/registry/domainRegistry.ts`
- Routes: `src/shared/constants/routes.ts` — includes **`ROUTES.service`** (`/service`) → `ServiceHubPage`; pass **`?serviceName=`** for deployment dashboard panel params (`{serviceName}` interpolation)

## Shared / API

- HTTP: `src/shared/api/api/client.ts`, decode: `src/shared/api/utils/decode.ts`
- Dashboard shell: `src/shared/components/ui/dashboard/` (`ConfigurableDashboard.tsx`, `dashboardPanelRegistry.tsx`)
- **uPlot:** `src/shared/components/ui/charts/UPlotChart.tsx` — on data-only updates (same options/geometry), call **`setData`** instead of destroying/recreating the chart. Dashboard panel renderers must build **`options` inside `useMemo`** (see `BarRenderer`, `ObservabilityChart`) so a new object is not created every render; otherwise **`mergedOptions` changes** and the chart tears down even when data shape is unchanged.

## Global refresh / auto-refresh

- **Zustand:** `src/app/store/appStore.ts` — `triggerRefresh()` increments **`refreshKey`** (also bumps on time-range changes).
- **TanStack Query:** Many hooks include `refreshKey` in `queryKey` to force refetch when the time window is unchanged (e.g. absolute range + manual/auto refresh). Use **`placeholderData: keepPreviousData`** (or `(p) => p`) on queries so refetches do not flash empty/loading UI.
- **Backend-driven dashboard panels** (`useComponentDataFetcher`, `useDataSourceFetcher`): **do not** put `refreshKey` in `queryKey` — that creates a new cache entry every tick and blinks the grid. Use stable keys (`component-query` / `datasource` + team + endpoint + time bounds) and **`useInvalidateQueriesOnAppRefresh`** to `invalidateQueries` when `refreshKey` changes. Treat **loading** as `isPending && data === undefined`, not `isLoading`, so background refetch does not flip cards to “loading”.
- **Header UI:** `src/app/layout/Header.tsx` + `src/shared/hooks/useAutoRefresh.ts` — interval auto-refresh calls `triggerRefresh`; the hook also ticks a clock for the “Xs ago” tooltip (throttled) so the header does not re-render every second.

